7:
It feels a bit empty without the ads
everywhere, but other than that... I
could get used to it.
15: Oh, uh, I was about to go shopping.
18:
Let me join you. You're the target of
my investigation, I can't very well let
you out of my sight, can I?
21:
Sure. Actually, that'd be a big help.
Everyone else happened to be very
busy today.
24:
Which is to say you need someone
to hold your bags. Fine, seeing as
our interests align, I can
accommodate you.
30:
It's no use! I was real careful scoping
this place out. I know exactly when
the security patrols, they won't—
32:
I'll clean this up in three minutes or
less.
41: Damn it... Just who are you?
44:
How disappointing. Oh well.
Hope you learned your lesson.
49:
Sorry for the trouble... and thank you
for seeing me all the way back
home.
51:
In the future, please refrain from
walking alone in suspicious places.
53:
If you're still worried, I recommend
signing a contract with 3MM, so—
56:
Ah. I'm sorry, forget that. I'm not on
the clock right now.
60:
Oh, you're just like a knight! Riding
out there and saving people, you're
so amazing!
65:
That's right! Oh, if you wouldn't mind,
please take this. It's the least I could
do.
68:
It... it's really nothing. I was only
doing what had to be done.
71: Thank you so much for everything!
75:
Someone's been in a good mood
ever since we got back.
87:
I... I guess I am. I had a bit of a
nostalgic blast-from-the-past, you
could say.
90:
I used to be obsessed with comic
book heroes, you see. When I was
young.
94: That's why you decided to join 3MM?
97:
Yeah. Though I've still got a long way
to go—I need more experience
under my belt.
99:
Of course, reality is a bit less... neat
and tidy than our dreams. Especially
so when you work for a massive
corporation.
102:
But I knew that going in to it. It's no
problem.
104:
Sometimes I get the feeling that I've
lost track of what I was really after.
That I've forgotten my original goal.
107:
Heh. Me, a knight. I had the worst
grades in saber training out of my
whole class, you know?
111:
Saber training? You mean... beam
sabers?!
115:
Heh. What is it about beam sabers
that makes boys' eyes go wide like
that?
118:
This is just between us, but that hero
from the comic I like also used a
beam saber.
122:
I really wanted to get good at it, so I
kept at it for a while. I eventually
gave up, but I sure put in a lot of
effort.
125:
You really looked up to that hero,
huh?
129:
Eh. Honestly? Guns are better for the
types of jobs I do.
132:
Turns out bullets are faster than
swords. And the whole
long-distance thing is too good to
pass up.
136:
You certainly know your way around
a firearm, considering your
performance today.
140:
...I was kind of hoping you'd disagree
with my previous statement, seeing
as you're a sword user.
145:
Why? Are swords truly faster than
bullets?!
150:
No, Light! She's just being cheeky.
Swords are not faster than bullets.
154:
You'd hope the legendary
Champion would know something
like that...
